  "summary": "EscalaFlow is a clean 3-workspace monorepo (13 API files, 46 web files, 3 shared files) ready for Electron migration. The API layer is thin (34 HTTP endpoints, all SQL inline in route handlers) — conversion to IPC is mechanical. The motor (gerador.ts 777 lines + validador.ts 393 lines) takes a db parameter via DI, making worker thread adaptation clean. The React frontend is 100% complete with 8 pages, 7 custom components, 17 shadcn/ui components, and 8 service files that wrap a single fetch client. The migration is fundamentally a plumbing job: swap HTTP for IPC, move files to Electron directory structure, handle native module compilation. Business logic and UI remain untouched. Critical risks are native module builds (RISK-01/02) and BrowserRouter incompatibility with file:// protocol (RISK-03). Total estimated file operations: 35 moves, 9 rewrites, 7 creates, 3 directory deletes.",
